<theme id="thm222">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Groups of two 16th notes</title>
<tocimage>img222.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson the next patterns are introduced:</para>

<score>
    <music>
    (score (vers 1.6)
      (instrument
        (musicData
        (time 2 8 noVisible)(r e)(n * s g+)(n * s g-)(barline double)
        (n * s g+)(n * s g-)(r e)(barline end)
    )))
    </music>
</score>

<part><title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>

<score>
    <control_play />
    <control_measures />
    <music>
    (score (vers 1.6)
      (instrument
        (musicData
        (clef G)(key C)(time 2 8)(r e)(n a4 s g+)(n a4 s g-)(barline)
        (n a4 s g+)(n a4 s g-)(r e)(barline end)
    )))
    </music>
</score>
</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm222_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear: 8th rest and two
16th notes.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm222_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Train your ear: Two 16th notes
and 8th rest.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm222_E3">Exercise 3</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

